# Phase 2, Step 4: More Triggers

Add autonomous triggers so the agent can wake up without user input.

## Goal

Add a file watcher and a clock alongside the existing REPL trigger.

## Requirements

- `WATCH_DIR` env var: watch a directory with `fs.watch`, fire on changes
- `CRON_SCHEDULE` env var: `*/N * * * *` style interval, fire periodically
- `CRON_PROMPT` env var: the message sent to the agent on each clock tick
- All triggers feed into `handleTrigger(source, message)` which pushes to history and runs `agentLoop()`
- Messages are prefixed with `[source]` so the agent knows how it was woken
- Debounce file watcher (500ms) to batch rapid changes
- `busy` flag prevents overlapping runs from concurrent triggers
- No external dependencies — uses built-in `fs.watch` and `setInterval`

## Key Concepts

- Three trigger sources: REPL (user), file watcher, clock
- All feed into the same agent loop — the agent doesn't care how it was woken
- Triggers are opt-in via env vars — omit them and only REPL runs

## What changes from Step 3

- Extract `handleTrigger()` that all sources call
- Add `startFileWatcher()` using `fs.watch` with debounce
- Add `startClock()` parsing `*/N` minute intervals
- docker-compose passes new env vars
